==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Agnostic
<hw>Ag*nos"tic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ knowing, <?/ to know.]</ety> <def>Professing
ignorance; involving no dogmatic; pertaining to or involving
agnosticism.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ag*nos"tic*al*ly</wf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agnostic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Agnostic
<hw>Ag*nos"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who professes ignorance, or
denies that we have any knowledge, save of phenomena; one who supports
agnosticism, neither affirming nor denying the existence of a personal
Deity, a future life, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>agnostical</ent>⟦br⟧
